  "description": "Archival ingest package for Aberdeen Group's October 2004 benchmark report analyzing IT budget and spending trends across 170+ enterprises. The study uses the PACE (Pressures, Actions, Capabilities, Enablers) framework and Aberdeen Competitive Framework to link IT budget process maturity to cost performance and customer satisfaction outcomes. Key finding: 15-25% of IT investment wasted industry-wide; best-in-class firms spend 10-25% less as percent of revenue.",
